        		</div>
        	</div>
        </div> The crux of the issue is that a referendum question (however the minister chooses to word it) may well be interpreted as a mandate to go forward with amalgamation in some fashion, and because it is a referendum question, councillors would have to withhold comment on the issue and staff would not be able to provide any details on the implications. The alternative is to have formal and informal discussions prior to a referendum of any kind -- and presumably then you could have a clear yes/no referendum.
        				</blockquote>
        			</div>
        
        			
        
        
        		</div>
        			
        
                                	
        		         
        			
        
        			
        		</div>
        	</div>
